    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Policy options and recommendations developed for specific policy issues
- Increased in awareness and recognition of the humanistic and empathetic values in the policy process by policymakers
- Alternative ways created to design policies to tackle complex problems that are arising in Thailand that cannot easily be resolved by traditional policy processes
- Government officials and policy makers are able to apply innovative tools to public service delivery and policy formulation
- Increased in NESDC&apos;s capacity to champion policy innovation for development solutions
- Increased in public e-participation in policymaking
- Increased application of information and knowledge on innovation in policy making
- Increased in the visibility of NESDC in being a knowledge champion in policy innovation and a progressive policy think-tank agency
- A larger and stronger network of innovators who are open to new ideas and new ways of working</narrative>
    </description>
